Cook pasta according to package directions. Add broccoli to pot in last 4 minutes of cooking time. Drain and rinse under cold water; transfer to large bowl. Add edamame; toss well. Whisk together teriyaki sauce, vinegar, vegetable oil, honey, garlic and pepper; reserve 2 tbsp (30 mL) dressing. Drizzle remaining dressing over pasta mixture; toss to coat well. Transfer to serving platter. Top with sliced steak; drizzle with reserved dressing. Sprinkle with green onions and sesame seeds.